{"name":"Art of Command","type":"item","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You've observed a good leader and figured out how to hone your strategies. Once per Scene, you can give an order to one of your allies and if they try to carry it out, they will receive 2 Additional Successes to any Check.","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Withstand an onslaught from Enar by fighting alongside Andersen.","scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","notes":"This Gift is learned by observing Andersen's tactical command during battle. The Hunter must fight alongside Andersen during one of Enar's attacks (Day 1, 2, or 3) and survive the encounter. The order must be specific and tactical. This Gift is similar to Andersen's 'Commander' Gift but slightly less powerful (once per Scene vs. 3 times per Scene)."},"_id":"8733902a5d285313"}
{"name":"Blessing of the Sea","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/water/orb-ice-opaque.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You are blessed by the mighty Sea Fairy and therefore sea-related abilities have no effect on you. You receive 2 Additional Successes on each Defense Check you make to defend yourself against a Gift, spell, or action made using a Descriptor that includes the word 'sea'.","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Prove to the Sea Fairy your intention to do something for poor Enar.","scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","notes":"This blessing protects against Enar's 'Rage of the Sea' Gift and any other sea-based threats. The Sea Fairy grants this after the Hunter demonstrates compassion for Enar rather than just wanting to kill him. The blessing is permanent for the Scenario but only affects sea-related powers."},"_id":"056390537e2d41fe"}
{"name":"Coral of the Sea Fairy","type":"item","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/pearl-pink.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You dispatched that hateful fairy and harnessed her soul in a lump of coral. Now her power is yours. You can use 1 Treasure Token to unlock this Gift for the duration of the Scenario. Spend 1 Soma to tap into the Coral's power and choose one of the following effects: **1. Water of Life:** A target recovers 1 Wound. **2. The Fury of the Sea:** The water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all threats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense Check against OL Hard 7 to avoid being overwhelmed by the waves and being thrown away, suffering 1 Wound. **3. The Waves of the Sea:** You can travel to any point of the sea within 6 miles. This shift is instantaneous and you can take up to 2 subjects with you. **CURSE:** Sea creatures sense what you have done and will attack you without hesitation to try to free the soul of the Fairy.","somaCost":1,"requirement":"Kill the Sea Fairy. (Special gift for Marina the Sea Explorer only)","scenario":"A Soldier's Duty","notes":"This is a DARK Gift only available to Marina the Sea Explorer if she murders the Sea Fairy. The Fairy refuses to help Marina initially due to her selfish reputation. If Marina kills her anyway, she can trap the Fairy's soul in coral and steal her powers. Requires spending 1 Treasure Token to unlock, then costs 1 Soma per use. The curse is permanent: all sea creatures (fish, whales, merfolk, sea monsters, etc.) become hostile and attack Marina on sight to free the trapped soul. This is a morally dark choice with serious consequences. The coral must be carried on Marina's person."},"_id":"935f46e4330faa68"}